column5: Visited both of the Lake Huron Fishing Club Trout & Salmon Hatcheries this week & took a little video, things are looking good for this years crop & our Brown Trout eggs should be here by the end of the month & a full house we'll have.Tight Lines SBK  http://lhfcschoolhatcheries.blogspot.ca/2014/12/7-month-old-rainbow-trout-15-month-old.html
Awesome! Do you know where these are going?

Rainbows are going in the Saugeen, Salmon mostly in the Saugeen & our Browns already went along the Lake Huron shore line from around Point Clark to Pike Bay & maybe some out of Barrow Bay, I didn't hear this year. Tight Lines SBK

That's awesome! Thanks for the info! I would love to get involved and help out with some of the stocking programs, guess its time to do some research as exams are almost over ahaha Thanks again SBK! Tight Lines!
c10 where are you from Tight Lines SBK
Burlington, am In Waterloo at the moment for schooling though, yourself?

Cool, pretty far away but if you know of any places that want or need help my name is Chris, I am always interested in that sort of stuff.  Or let me know if you are ever down in the south and wanted to go out fishing eh! ahaha
